label.value: Old or Age Indeterminate Septal Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V1, V2 and often V3, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the intraventricular septum, without evidence of current or ongoing acute infarction. (CDISC)
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to pairing events.
A unit of measurement of the number of entities per unit of area equal to one hundred high powered fields.

label.value: Predicted Volume of Distribution Normalized by Dose

value.value: The volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following intravascular administration, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the dose.
Supplying or being a probable or reasonable settlement or result.
A previous episode of failure by a patient to follow medical advice, take medication as directed, or adhere to a prescribed course of treatment.
The categorization of individuals with or without the potential for having tuberculosis.

A synthetic glucocorticoid with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulating properties. Upon administration, budesonide binds to intracellular glucocorticoid receptors (GRs) and induces the expression of glucocorticoid-responsive genes that encode for anti-inflammatory mediators, such as certain anti-inflammatory cytokines, including interleukin 10 (IL-10), and lipocortins. Lipocortins inhibit phospholipase A2, thereby blocking the release of arachidonic acid from membrane phospholipids and preventing the synthesis of prostaglandins and leukotrienes, both mediators of inflammation. In addition, budesonide prevents the release of pro-inflammatory cytokines from epithelial cells and macrophages, including interleukin 6 (IL-6), IL-8, interferon-beta (IFNb), and inhibits nuclear factor kappa-B (NF-kB) activation thereby decreasing NF-kB-mediated inflammation.
A regimen consisting of prednisone, cytarabine, 6-thioguanine, cyclophosphamide, and vincristine that may be used in the treatment of childhood acute myeloid leukemia (AML).
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to procedure.
An electrocardiographic finding in which the frontal plane QRS axis cannot be calculated.
The reason the treatment was administered.
The reason the drug or therapy was temporarily ceased.
The reason the treatment was not administered.

label.value: Refugee From High Tuberculosis Prevalent Area

value.value: An individual that has fled a country for their own safety which has a high occurrence of tuberculosis.

label.value: Repolarization Abnormality Secondary To Ventricular Hypertrophy

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of ST depression and T wave inversion in the presence of increased QRS amplitude which are thought to be due to left ventricular hypertrophy.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to reproductive system findings.
The environment within which the person may have come into contact with a disease carrier, or played the role of a disease carrier.
An electrocardiographic finding of a QT interval corrected for heart rate that is shorter than the lower limit of normal. Thresholds for different age, gender, and patient populations exist. (CDISC)
The physical location at which the medication or therapy was observed, by the healthcare provider, as being taken by the subject.
Social factors such as personal behavior, lifestyle, or environment belonging to the subject which are known to increase the likelihood of infection and disease.
The surroundings or environment in which social activities occur.

A public health activity for the determination of who transmitted a disease to another subject and whether this person: is still infectious; was reported to the health department as a disease case or suspect; or has infected others.

label.value: Subject in Contact With Tuberculosis Source

value.value: An individual that came into contact with a source of tuberculosis.
A drug serum concentration below therapeutic levels.
A lymph node located in a superficial part of the body.
Clinical evidence to support reason for re-treatment of disease.

label.value: T Wave Alternans by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding in which there are variations in the shape, amplitude, or direction of the T wave from one beat to the next.

label.value: Travel To High Burden Tuberculosis Country

value.value: Entry into one or more of the 22 countries that have a relatively high prevalence of tuberculosis cases.
An indication of whether this is the individual's first time being treated for a disease or that they are receiving a subsequent treatment.
The reason the drug or therapy was unsuccessful in treating the condition.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to tumor response.
Identification and clinical investigation of disease contacts.

label.value: Unifocal Atrial Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of premature atrial complexes which have a single distinct morphology, suggesting origin at one atrial site.

label.value: Unifocal Ventricular Premature Complex by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of premature ventricular complexes which have a single distinct morphology, suggesting origin at one ventricular site.
A subject domain utilized for the submission of information encompassing and representing data, vocabulary or records related to urinary system findings.
Source of information regarding the subject's vaccination status.
An electrocardiographic finding of normal sinus rhythm coexisting with a regular ectopic ventricular rhythm.

label.value: Volume of Distribution of Fraction Dose Observed Normalized by Dose

value.value: The volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following extravascular administration divided by the fraction of dose absorbed, calculated using the observed value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the dose.

label.value: Volume of Distribution of Fraction Dose Predicted Normalized by Dose

value.value: The volume of distribution associated with the terminal slope following extravascular administration divided by the fraction of dose absorbed, calculated using the predicted value of the last non-zero concentration, divided by the dose.

label.value: New Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of one or more regions of the heart and which is new compared to prior ECGs. No specification is provided for localization. (CDISC)

label.value: New Anterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V3 and V4, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anterior wall of the left ventricle and which is new compared to prior ECGs. (CDISC)

label.value: New Anterolateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V3 through V6, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anterolateral wall of the left ventricle and which is new compared to prior ECGs. (CDISC)

label.value: New Anteroseptal Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V1 through V4, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the anteroseptal wall of the left ventricle and which is new compared to prior ECGs. (CDISC)

label.value: New Extensive Anterior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads V1 to V6, I and aVL, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction involving the anterior and anterolateral walls of the left ventricle and which is new compared to prior ECGs. (CDISC)

label.value: New High Lateral Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads I and aVL, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the high lateral wall of the left ventricle and which is new compared to prior ECGs. (CDISC)

label.value: New Inferior Myocardial Infarction by ECG Finding

value.value: An electrocardiographic finding of pathologic Q waves in leads III, aVF and often II, which is suggestive of myocardial infarction of the inferior wall of the left ventricle and which is new compared to prior ECGs. (CDISC)
